text: Chan Sek Keong (born 5 November 1937) is a Singaporean former judge. He served as the third Chief Justice from 2006 until his retirement in 2012. He also served as Singapore's Attorney-General from 1992 to 2006. Chan was born in Ipoh, Perak, Malaya. His family were ethnic Chinese of a Cantonese background. ==References== Category:1937 births Category:Living people Category:Attorneys general Category:Chief justices Category:Singaporean politicians
